/* Define the variables */
VARIABLES
  NUMBER v_salary
  NUMBER v_tax
  NUMBER v_state_fee
  NUMBER v_exec_bonus
  TEXT   v_state
  TEXT   v_grade

/* Begin the formula */
FORMULA COLUMN Net_Pay

/* Assign the input values to the variables */
v_salary := 'SALARY';
v_state := 'STATE';
v_grade := 'GRADE';

/* Calculate the tax based on the salary */
IF v_salary > 120000 THEN
  v_tax := v_salary * 0.03; /* High-income tax */
ELSIF v_salary >= 80000 AND v_salary <= 120000 THEN
  v_tax := v_salary * 0.02; /* Mid-income tax */
ELSE
  v_tax := v_salary * 0.01; /* Low-income tax */
END IF;

/* Apply the state fee for California employees */
IF v_state = 'CA' THEN
  v_state_fee := 50;
ELSE
  v_state_fee := 0;
END IF;

/* Add the executive bonus for MGR or higher grades */
IF v_grade = 'MGR' OR v_grade > 'MGR' THEN
  v_exec_bonus := 500;
ELSE
  v_exec_bonus := 0;
END IF;

/* Calculate the net pay */
RETURN v_salary - v_tax - v_state_fee + v_exec_bonus;

END FORMULA;
```

This formula will calculate the net pay based on the salary, state, and job grade. It applies the appropriate tax rate, adds a state fee for California employees, and adds an executive bonus for managers or higher grades. The final net pay is returned as the result.
